HEADWORD: Praseodymium
<hw>Pra`se*o*dym"i*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Praseo-</ets> + di<ets>dymium</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An elementary substance, one of the constituents
of didymium; -- so called from the green color of its salts. Symbol Ps.
Atomic weight 143.6.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

